'''John Harris''' (born [[July 29]], [[1940s|1948]], in [[Wikipedia:London|London]]) is a [[Wikipedia:British people|British]] artist<ref name="Biography" /> who painted the covers of three ''[[Star Wars]]'' books: ''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Tide I: Onslaught|Dark Tide I: Onslaught]]'',<ref name="Onslaught">{{WebCite|url=https://www.alisoneldred.com/john-harris/originals-for-sale-1/sci-fi-book-art-4/1146-star-wars-the-new-jedi-order-dark-tideonslaught/|text=John Harris Originals for sale: Sci Fi Book Art - Star Wars: The New Jedi Order, Dark Tide/Onslaught|work=Alison Eldred artists' agent|archivedate=20250315214223}}</ref> ''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Tide II: Ruin|Dark Tide II: Ruin]]''<ref name="Ruin">{{WebCite|url=https://www.alisoneldred.com/john-harris/originals-for-sale-1/sci-fi-book-art-1/3302-star-wars-the-new-jedi-order-dark-tide-ii-ruin/|text=John Harris Originals for sale: Sci Fi Book Art - Star Wars, The New Jedi Order, Dark Tide II, Ruin|work=Alison Eldred artists' agent|archivedate=20250405162144}}</ref> and ''[[Death Star (novel)|Death Star]]''. His preliminary painting for ''Death Star'' was purchased by [[George Lucas]] for his personal collection.<ref name="Death Star">{{WebCite|url=https://www.alisoneldred.com/john-harris/originals-for-sale-1/sci-fi-book-art-5/881-death-star/|text=John Harris Originals for sale: Sci Fi Book Art - Death Star|work=Alison Eldred artists' agent|archivedate=20240620083215}}</ref>

Harris began painting at age fourteen, and he graduated from a Fine Arts program at the [[Wikipedia:University of Exeter|University of Exeter]] in [[1970]]. In either [[1984]] or [[1985]], he was invited by [[Wikipedia:NASA|NASA]] to witness and paint a [[Wikipedia:Space Shuttle program|Space Shuttle]] launch; the resulting painting hangs in the [[Wikipedia:Kennedy Space Center|Kennedy Space Center]] and is part of the [[Wikipedia:Smithsonian Institution|Smithsonian]] collection.<ref name="Biography" />

Harris began to paint book covers in the 1980s, and his artwork has appeared on works by authors such as [[Wikipedia:John Scalzi|John Scalzi]], [[Wikipedia:Ben Bova|Ben Bova]], [[Wikipedia:Jack McDevitt|Jack McDevitt]], and [[Wikipedia:Orson Scott Card|Orson Scott Card]].<ref name="Biography" /> Harris has twice been nominated for the [[Wikipedia:Hugo Award for Best Professional Artist|Hugo Award for Best Professional Artist]],<ref name="Hugo 1">{{WebCite|url=http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/2008-hugo-awards/|text=2008 Hugo Awards|work=World Science Fiction Society|archivedate=20110507164815}}</ref><ref name="Hugo 2">{{WebCite|url=http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/2014-hugo-awards/|text=2014 Hugo Awards|work=World Science Fiction Society|archivedate=20150906071016}}</ref> and in [[2015]] he won the [[Wikipedia:Chesley Award for Lifetime Artistic Achievement|Chesley Award for Lifetime Artistic Achievement]].<ref name="Biography" />

